# Architecture Documentation (Diagramwright)

The canonical architecture document for this project is **`docs/ARCHITECTURE.md`**.
(This overrides the generic `ARCHITECTURE.md` path referenced by the shared
`doc-automation` rule.)

## When to update `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md`
Update it when changing:
- Directory structure or adding/removing modules
- Core component responsibilities (web UI, stores, MCP server, sync bridge)
- Data flow between components (local editing loop or agent collaboration loop)
- Technology stack or dependencies
- The MCP tool/resource surface or the HTTP/SSE bridge contract

## Keep in sync
- The embedded Mermaid **System Overview** diagram in `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md`
  mirrors the app's built-in example diagram in
  `src/lib/graph/defaultNodes.ts` (`EXAMPLE_DIAGRAM`). When one changes,
  update the other.
- Link new top-level docs from `README.md`.

## Style
- Concise but comprehensive; prefer tables and code blocks over prose.
- Only factual, implementation-based content — no placeholders or hypothetical dates.
